<p>I would like to have the standard Android menu ( ActionBar Overflow Menu ) with the scrollbar always on when there is enough items so the user has to scroll. </p>  <p>The original Android version has the scrollbar fade a second or two after displayed and this is what I do not want. I want the scroll bar to never fade nor disappear. </p>  <p>I have tried to do so programmatically but have not been able. </p>  <p>I have decided to go to styles. Still cannot do so. Here is the code : </p>  <p>IN STYLES.XML : </p>  <pre><code>&lt;resources&gt;  &lt;!-- Base application theme. --&gt; &lt;style name="AppTheme" parent="Theme.AppCompat.Light.DarkActionBar"&gt;     &lt;!-- Customize your theme here. --&gt;      &lt;!-- SSB --&gt;     &lt;item name="android:popupMenuStyle"&gt;@style/newPopupMenuStyle&lt;/item&gt;     &lt;!-- SSB --&gt;  &lt;/style&gt;  &lt;!-- SSB --&gt; &lt;style name="newPopupMenuStyle" parent="@android:style/Widget.PopupMenu"&gt;      &lt;item name="android:fadeScrollbars"&gt;false&lt;/item&gt;     &lt;item name="android:scrollbarFadeDuration"&gt;0&lt;/item&gt;     &lt;item name="android:scrollbarDefaultDelayBeforeFade"&gt;0&lt;/item&gt;  &lt;/style&gt; &lt;!-- SSB --&gt;  &lt;/resources&gt; </code></pre>  <p>IN MENU.XML : </p>  <pre><code>&lt;menu xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android" xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto" xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools" tools:context=".MainActivity" style="@style/newPopupMenuStyle"&gt;  //Items, groups, submenus here.  &lt;/menu&gt;  </code></pre>  <p>Please, help! </p>